526.blender_r Flags

These are flags that appear in the benchmark sources, categorized as to whether they are portability candidates, mandatory, or forbidden.

Sections

Selecting one of the following will take you directly to that section:

  • Portability Flags
  • Mandatory Flags
  • Forbidden Flags

Portability Flags

  • -DSPEC_NO_INLINE
  • -DSPEC_NO_MKDTEMP
  • -DSPEC_ALIGNFIX
  • -DSPEC_NEED_ALLOCA_H
  • -DSPEC_NEED_IEEEFP_H
  • -DSPEC_FNM_MACROS
  • -DHAVE_LIMITS_H
  • -DHAVE_STDBOOL_H
  • -DHAVE_UNISTD_H
  • -DFREE_WINDOWS
  • -DFREE_WINDOWS64
  • -DHAVE__BOOL
  • -DPATH_MAX
  • -DSPEC_GLMULDEFS
  • -DSPEC_HAVE_S_IFDIR
  • -DSPEC_LINUX
  • -DSPEC_NO_ISFINITE
  • -DSPEC_PNG_NO_FLOAT
  • -DSPEC_PNG_NO_SETJMP
  • -DWIN32
  • -DWIN64
  • -D_FILE_OFFSET_BITS
  • -D_LARGEFILE64_SOURCE
  • -D_LARGEFILE_SOURCE
  • -D_PTRDIFF_T_
  • -D_SSIZE_T_
  • -D__BIG_ENDIAN__
  • -D__BOOL_DEFINED
  • -D__LITTLE_ENDIAN__
  • -D__STDC_LIMIT_MACROS
    • -DSPEC_NO_INLINE
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DSPEC_NO_INLINE(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Defining this macro will cause the sources to be generated without any instances of the "inline" keyword used. It may be necessary to use this when building using a compiler that ignores inline functions when inlining is disabled.

    • -DSPEC_NO_MKDTEMP
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DSPEC_NO_MKDTEMP(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Defining this macro will cause the benchmark to not attempt to use the mkdtemp() function.

    • -DSPEC_ALIGNFIX
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DSPEC_ALIGNFIX(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Defining this macro will cause some structs to have members added which are intended to cause subsequent members to be aligned such that they do not cause misaligned access failures on systems where such failures are possible. Has no effect when the SPEC_LP64 macro is also defined.

    • -DSPEC_NEED_ALLOCA_H
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DSPEC_NEED_ALLOCA_H(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Defining this macro will cause alloca.h to be included for affected sources on compilation systems that need it.

    • -DSPEC_NEED_IEEEFP_H
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DSPEC_NEED_IEEEFP_H(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • When set, causes <ieeefp.h> to be included to get prototypes for functions like finite(), etc.

    • -DSPEC_FNM_MACROS
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DSPEC_FNM_MACROS(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • When set, (re)defines macros used by code that calls the fnmatch() function.

    • -DHAVE_LIMITS_H
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DHAVE_LIMITS_H(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Inclusion of system limits file in md5 src

    • -DHAVE_STDBOOL_H
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DHAVE_STDBOOL_H(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Helps define boolean types on a build system.

    • -DHAVE_UNISTD_H
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DHAVE_UNISTD_H(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • May be required for internal zlib

    • -DFREE_WINDOWS
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DFREE_WINDOWS(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Affects different function naming and typedefs relative to the MSVC and non-MSVC windows libraries

    • -DFREE_WINDOWS64
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DFREE_WINDOWS64(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Affects different function naming and typedefs relative to the MSVC and non-MSVC windows libraries

    • -DHAVE__BOOL
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DHAVE__BOOL(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Bool definition flexibility

    • -DPATH_MAX
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DPATH_MAX(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Flexibility for file io buffer sizes

    • -DSPEC_GLMULDEFS
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DSPEC_GLMULDEFS(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • GL function symbols that may be required for linking

    • -DSPEC_HAVE_S_IFDIR
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DSPEC_HAVE_S_IFDIR(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Flexibility for file I/O macros needed to compile

    • -DSPEC_LINUX
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DSPEC_LINUX(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Linux portability

    • -DSPEC_NO_ISFINITE
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DSPEC_NO_ISFINITE(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Choice of finite detection functional call for floats

    • -DSPEC_PNG_NO_FLOAT
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DSPEC_PNG_NO_FLOAT(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Flexibility for PNG library symbols

    • -DSPEC_PNG_NO_SETJMP
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DSPEC_PNG_NO_SETJMP(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Flexibility for PNG library symbols

    • -DWIN32
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DWIN32(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • For Win32 API and library portability

    • -DWIN64
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DWIN64(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • For Win64 (and Win32) API and library portability

    • -D_FILE_OFFSET_BITS
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]D_FILE_OFFSET_BITS(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Helps with stat(...) related datastructure compatiblity and various filesystems

    • -D_LARGEFILE64_SOURCE
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]D_LARGEFILE64_SOURCE(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Enable Large File SUpport extension interface functions.

    • -D_LARGEFILE_SOURCE
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]D_LARGEFILE_SOURCE(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Enable Large File Support extension interface functions.

    • -D_PTRDIFF_T_
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]D_PTRDIFF_T_(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Offer portability for system's availability of ptrdiff_t. Commonly, found in stddef.h.

    • -D_SSIZE_T_
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]D_SSIZE_T_(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Offer portability for systems availability of ssize_t.

    • -D__BIG_ENDIAN__
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]D__BIG_ENDIAN__(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Backup endianness toggle

    • -D__BOOL_DEFINED
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]D__BOOL_DEFINED(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Some systems need to see alternate definitions for boolean types. This flag enables their use.

    • -D__LITTLE_ENDIAN__
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]D__LITTLE_ENDIAN__(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • Backup endianess toggle

    • -D__STDC_LIMIT_MACROS
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]D__STDC_LIMIT_MACROS(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • This flag may be needed to avoid C99 type redefinitions depending on your C header implementation.

    • This flag is included automatically by Spec/object.pm.

    • -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_action, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_buttons, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_clip, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_console, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_file, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_graph, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_image, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_info, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_logic

    • This flag is included automatically by Spec/object.pm.

    • -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_nla, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_node, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_outliner, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_script, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_sequencer, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_text, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_time, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_userpref, -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_view3d
    • -Iblender/source/blender/editors/space_(?:nla|node|outliner|script|sequencer|text|time|userpref|view3d)(?:\s+|$)

    • This flag is included automatically by Spec/object.pm.

    • -Iblender/extern/binreloc/include, -Iblender/extern/colamd/Include, -Iblender/extern/glew/include, -Iblender/extern/libmv, -Iblender/extern/libmv/intern, -Iblender/extern/rangetree, -Iblender/extern/wcwidth
    • -Iblender/extern/(?:binreloc|colamd|glew|libmv|rangetree|wcwidth)(?i:/include|/intern)?(?:\s+|$)

    • This flag is included automatically by Spec/object.pm.

    • -Iblender/intern, -Iblender/intern/atomic, -Iblender/intern/audaspace/intern, -Iblender/intern/cycles/blender, -Iblender/intern/elbeem/extern, -Iblender/intern/ghost, -Iblender/intern/ghost/intern, -Iblender/intern/glew-mx, -Iblender/intern/glew-mx/intern
    • -Iblender/intern(?:/atomic|/audaspace|/cycles/blender|/elbeem|/ghost|/glew-mx)?(?:/intern|/extern)?(?:\s+|$)

    • This flag is included automatically by Spec/object.pm.

    • -Iblender/intern/guardedalloc, -Iblender/intern/guardedalloc/intern, -Iblender/intern/iksolver/extern, -Iblender/intern/locale, -Iblender/intern/memutil, -Iblender/intern/mikktspace, -Iblender/intern/opencolorio, -Iblender/intern/raskter, -Iblender/intern/smoke/extern, -Iblender/intern/string, -Iblender/intern/utfconv
    • -Iblender/intern/(?:guardedalloc|iksolver|locale|memutil|mikktspace|opencolorio|raskter|smoke|string|utfconv)(?:/intern|/extern)?(?:\s+|$)

    • This flag is included automatically by Spec/object.pm.

    • -DGLEW_NO_ES
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DGLEW_NO_ES(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • This flag disables the use of OpenGL for Embedded Systems APIs. It is automatically supplied by the benchmark.

    • -DGLEW_STATIC
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DGLEW_STATIC(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • This flag indicates that the OpenGL code is not being built for use in a dynamic library. It is automatically supplied by the benchmark.

    • -DWITH_DNA_GHASH
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DWITH_DNA_GHASH(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • This flag indicates that a hash data structure is used to speed lookups done while loading .blend files. It is automatically supplied by the benchmark.

    • -DWITH_GL_PROFILE_COMPAT
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DWITH_GL_PROFILE_COMPAT(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • This flag causes Ghost to use a basic OpenGL profile that does not rely on features in OpenGL ES. It is automatically supplied by the benchmark.

    • -DWITH_HEADLESS
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DWITH_HEADLESS(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • This flag indicates that the code will not be doing any on-screen presentation and eliminates the need for a windowing system. It is automatically supplied by the benchmark.

    • -DHAVE_UNSIGNED_CHAR
    • (?:^|(?<=\s))[-/]DHAVE_UNSIGNED_CHAR(?:\([^\)]+\))?(?:=\S*)?(?=\s|$)

    • This flag indicates that in the compilation system being used, the 'char' type is unsigned by default. This is sort of redundant, since most of the code assumes this property anyway, and doesn't work properly if that assumption is not correct.
